SIMPLE: unlimited
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlimited
<hw>Un*lim"it*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not limited;
having no bounds; boundless; <as>as, an <ex>unlimited</ex> expanse of
ocean</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Undefined; indefinite; not bounded by proper
exceptions; <as>as, <ex>unlimited</ex> terms</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Nothing
doth more prevail than <xex>unlimited</xex> generalities.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unconfined; not restrained; unrestricted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ascribe not unto God such an <qex>unlimited</qex> exercise of
mercy as may destroy his justice.</q> <rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unlimited problem</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>a
problem which is capable of an infinite number of solutions.</cd> --
<col><b>Unlimited pump</b></col>, <cd>a kind of deep-well pump placed at
the level of the water, and operated from above ground.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*lim"it*ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*lim"it*ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unline</ent>⟦br⟧
